public abstract class NamedConstructorMapper<T>
extends Object
implements org.springframework.jdbc.core.RowMapper<T>

Spring's RowMapper implementation using NamedConstructorList. Designed to use with immutable classes (with final fields) - only constructor invocation is used without any field access. Constructor arguments must be annotated with JSR330 Named annotations (there are other ways to access constructor names in runtime,see paranamer project, but we use @Named annotations only). Constructors without @Named annotations on arguments will be ignored. Constructors with @Named annotations must have all they arguments annotated with not blank values without duplicates. All reflection introspection is done on mapper instantiation. @Named values used in case-insensitive mode (databases usually use column names so) so all @Named values and all result set column names must be locale insensitive. Supports class hierarchies - different subclasses instantiation from single result set based on, use builder(String) method to create subclasses mapper and see NamedConstructorSubclassesMapper for details.

Author:
alexkasko Date: 7/6/12
See Also:
NamedConstructor, NamedConstructorList, NamedConstructorSingleMapper, NamedConstructorSubclassesMapper
